post_cb({"39442185": {"ParentId": "39442136", "LastEditDate": "2016-09-12T01:37:37.383", "CommentCount": "4", "CreationDate": "2016-09-12T01:11:41.273", "OwnerUserId": "6471538", "LastEditorUserId": "6471538", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "39442185", "Score": "0", "Body": "<p>You could certainly do something like this:</p>\n<pre><code>int main()\n{\n    while(1==1) /* (1==1) is always true. */\n    {\n        /* Do the hokey pokey, turn yourself around, and do whatever else you feel like doing. */\n    }\n    /* The program will never reach this point unless you explicitly break out of the loop. */\n    return 0;\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>This will result in a program that just repeats over and over again until you kill it. This is, of course, bad style, but it will work if you just need to get something up and running quickly.</p>\n<p>As Trevor Hickey mentions, you could call <code>break</code> from within the loop and break out.</p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2016-09-12T01:37:37.383"}, "39442223": {"ParentId": "39442136", "LastEditDate": "2016-09-12T01:28:16.883", "CommentCount": "4", "CreationDate": "2016-09-12T01:16:35.683", "OwnerUserId": "4743711", "LastEditorUserId": "4743711", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "39442223", "Score": "5", "Body": "<p>The standard C++ says...</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_39442136_39442223_0\">5.2.2.9 Recursive calls are permitted, except to the function named main</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>\"<strong>The Standard</strong>\" at <a href=\"https://isocpp.org/std/the-standard\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://isocpp.org/std/the-standard</a></p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2016-09-12T01:28:16.883"}, "39442136": {"CommentCount": "9", "ViewCount": "72", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "6471538", "CreationDate": "2016-09-12T01:04:01.880", "LastActivityDate": "2016-09-12T01:37:37.383", "Title": "Can you return to main instead of returning 0", "AcceptedAnswerId": "39442223", "LastEditDate": "2016-09-12T01:15:36.710", "Id": "39442136", "Score": "-2", "Body": "<p>I am relearning C++. I was quite a noob before but I am going over the basics again and hopefully going further. My main question is, at the end of the main loop, is there a way to call the function again instead of ending the programme by returning 0. So something along the line of:</p>\n<pre><code>    ........\n    return main;\n}\n</code></pre>\n", "Tags": "<c++>", "OwnerUserId": "6820571", "AnswerCount": "2"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_39442136_39442223_0": {"section_id": 5996, "quality": 0.625, "length": 5}}, "n3337": {"so_39442136_39442223_0": {"section_id": 5764, "quality": 0.875, "length": 7}}, "n4659": {"so_39442136_39442223_0": {"section_id": 7497, "quality": 0.625, "length": 5}}}});